author: arj
msg: Web unit test scripts gain 3 more tests, which verify that JSPWiki users can 1) create new pages (no ACL), 2) create new pages with unrestricted view permissions and 3) create new pages with restricted view permissions.

author: arj
msg: Bug fix: test version of userdatabase.xml modified to include dummy created/lastModified timestamps. The lack thereof was creating scary (but entirely harmless) messages in jspwiki.log.

author: arj
msg: Bug fix: LoginContent's error message now correctly displays a "you don't have access to page __(foo)__" if the user needs to log in.

author: arj
msg: Bug fix: quick2Top and quick2Bottom markers no longer have an annoying underline. Credit: Dirk Frederickx.

author: arj
msg: Minor tweak to remove hard-coded wiki context lookups.
